        "question":  "Do you agree that it is important to have a work-life balance?",
        "answer":  "Position: Yes — work-life balance is not just desirable but essential for sustainable performance and wellbeing. Reason: Chronic overwork produces diminishing cognitive returns — after 50 hours per week, output per hour drops sharply and errors increase. Beyond productivity, chronic overwork increases risks of cardiovascular disease, depression, and burnout. A rested, healthy worker ultimately produces more value than an exhausted one. Example: Japan\u0027s karoshi culture — death from overwork — is a cautionary extreme. In response, Japan has implemented work-hour caps and mandatory annual leave. Meanwhile, companies like Microsoft Japan found that shifting to a four-day work week increased productivity by 40%, challenging the assumption that more hours means more output. Wrap-up: Work-life balance is not an indulgence — it is the sustainable foundation of long-term health, creativity, and professional excellence.",
